The paper deals with a communication problem involving the transmission of packets to multiple users, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of prior knowledge of linear combinations of packets suggests a potential connection to coding theory (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). The proposed algorithm for minimizing the rank of the derived matrix involves a randomized approach, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
